description: Today is International Holocaust Remembrance Day.     TIL about the MS St. Louis - a German ship most notable for a single voyage in 1939, in which its captain tried to find homes for 908 Jewish refugees from Germany.     After they were denied entry to Cuba, the USA and Canada, the refugees were returned to Europe and historians estimate approximately a quarter of them died in death camps during WWII ... .     To mark this day, @Stil_Manifest is tweeting the names & photos of victims of Nazism who were refused entry to North America - an incredibly powerful reminder that the past is not something we should "get over" - it's there to inform our present actions and guide our course into the future.
